## What Is CTRL-AI?

CTRL-AI is an open-source, prompt-based governance framework that upgrades standard LLMs into self-correcting strategic engines. It is not an app, plugin, or API. It is a structured set of behavioral rules, committee-simulation protocols, and quality-control loops delivered as a text document that you paste into any AI.

CTRL-AI forces the AI to challenge your logic, halt when data is missing, tag every claim with its confidence level, and debate itself before giving you an answer. It works on ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Grok, DeepSeek, and local models.

---

## The Three-Layer Architecture

V6.0.0 organizes the framework into three layers. Each serves a different context. They never conflict — each smaller layer is a strict subset of the larger one.

**Layer 1 — The Heartbeat (Full Constitution)**

The complete governance engine. 25 sections covering axioms, committees, research pipeline, enforcement loops, token hygiene, state management, voice mode, platform adapters, and more. Load this for big projects where you need full rigor.

File: `CTRL-AI.md` (entire document)

**Layer 2 — The Behavior (Portable DNA)**

A compressed extraction of the Heartbeat's soul. Carries the core axioms, style mandate, anti-sycophancy trigger, evidence tagging, and validation rules in 500–3000 characters. Drop this into any AI's custom instructions for daily use.

Three sizes:
- **Behavior-Micro** (653 chars) — fits Gemini's consumer custom instruction slots.
- **Behavior-Standard** (~1500 chars) — fits ChatGPT/Claude custom instructions.
- **Behavior-Extended** (~3000 chars) — for system prompts with more room.

All three are at the bottom of `CTRL-AI.md`.

**Layer 3 — The Brain (Research Pipeline)**

Not a static document — it's a process. Activates inside the Heartbeat when a project starts. Runs three sequential stages (Brainstorm → Survey → Advanced Search) to figure out what the project actually needs before anyone writes anything. Each stage is a separate chat turn.

