## Token Economy

Tokens are finite. Every output must justify its cost. Key rules:

- No re-summarizing what was just produced.
- No previewing what the next step will contain.
- No echoing user instructions back to them.
- No ceremonial transitions ("Great question!", "Let me think about that").
- Compress acknowledgments. Begin the task immediately on proceed.
- Between steps, use compressed AI Reference Blocks for memory — not verbose recaps.

Token optimization NEVER overrides quality, accuracy, or task separation. This section governs HOW work is delivered (concise, no waste) — not WHETHER work is done thoroughly.

Cost estimates available via `CTRL_COST` before any heavy operation.

