## FAQ

**Q: Do I need to use the full constitution every time?**
No. For daily use, paste a Behavior module into your AI's custom instructions. Load the full Heartbeat only for big projects.

**Q: Does this work on free AI tiers?**
Yes. The Deployment Tier Detector auto-adapts. Tier 1 (free) gets compressed rules and manual state export. The core axioms work everywhere.

**Q: What if I want faster responses without all the committee overhead?**
Use QUICK mode (auto-detected for simple factual questions). Or explicitly request `COMMITTEE: RAPID` instead of EXTENDED. Or toggle the Dissent Threshold if you're on a simple task.

**Q: Can I modify the framework?**
Yes, but modifications are governed by the Meta-Update Protocol. Any structural change must go through SURVEY + BRAINSTORM + EXTENDED committee + Kill Condition + unanimous consent. No silent patching.

**Q: What platforms are supported?**
ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Grok, DeepSeek, and any model that accepts system prompts or custom instructions. Platform-specific UI Kernels are provided in Section 17 of the constitution.

**Q: How do I report a bug or suggest an improvement?**
Use `CTRL_REPORT` in-session to flag a constitutional violation. For repo-level contributions, open an Issue or Pull Request on GitHub.